This research is motivated by the need to develop LIDAR in the context of remote sensing. Currently, LIDARs have various applications in geology and atmospheric physics: detecting the Seattle Fault through dense vegetation cover \cite{Harding:2000a}, mapping glaciers \cite{Hopkinson:2001a}, conducting planatery surveys (MOLA) \cite{Neumann:2001a}, and atmospheric monitoring \cite{Fernald:1984a}--\cite{Goldsmith:1998a}.

